All in all, it was three hours of what we expected: he's firmly in control, he's not making any drastic changes, and his rivals are SOL. 9/9
On the other hand, he cast aspersions on Jewish connection to the land and threatened to rescind Palestinian recognition of Israel.
To his credit, he condemned terror and defended Oslo, two state solution, and decision to send firefighters and attend Peres funeral.
He also took some shots at the US, for instance when talking about the UN in 2012: "The 'great state' didn't even want us to be an observer"
For instance: "I'd like to thank the Fatah Central Committee, which is still * the central committee *" --> a clear shot at Dahlan
This was pure political consolidation. For 3 hours, Abbas defended his positions, praised his loyalists, and chided his rivals.
Abbas was routinely interrupted by supporters yelling: 'with our blood, with our spirit, we sacrifice for you Abu Mazen"
This was the *actual* opening of the congress. There was dancing & singing for 30 minutes before Abbas arrived (none of that yesterday)
I don't know why Abbas delayed the speech a day, but the effect was notable: about half the members of the press there y'day were gone today
